<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="583" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1772,2016]" pageId="4" pageNumber="583">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1844,1871]" pageId="4" pageNumber="583">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Medium-sized species (
<quantity box="[590,680,1845,1871]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="583" unit="mm" value="3.9">3.9 mm</quantity>
). Dorsal punctation on head, pronotum and elytra moderately coarse and sparse. Mesoventral process strongly elevated, laminar, projected between mesocoxae (
<figureCitation box="[1163,1245,1881,1907]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–14" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1858,1883]" captionTargetBox="[164,1425,496,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[154,1434,488,1832]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–14. Habitus of hydrophilids found in the State of Piauí, Brazil. 9–10) Enochrus sp.: 9, dorsal view; 10, ventral view. 11–12) Helochares (Sindolus) femoratus (Brullé, 1841): 11, dorsal view; 12, ventral view. 13–14) Hydrobiomorpha spatula Bachmann, 1988: 13, dorsal view; 14, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3762192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3762192/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="583">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Last abdominal ventrite deeply notched, U-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[548,631,1917,1943]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–14" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1858,1883]" captionTargetBox="[164,1425,496,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[154,1434,488,1832]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–14. Habitus of hydrophilids found in the State of Piauí, Brazil. 9–10) Enochrus sp.: 9, dorsal view; 10, ventral view. 11–12) Helochares (Sindolus) femoratus (Brullé, 1841): 11, dorsal view; 12, ventral view. 13–14) Hydrobiomorpha spatula Bachmann, 1988: 13, dorsal view; 14, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3762192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3762192/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="583">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Parameres longer than median lobe; apices rounded; dorsal lobule narrow, swollen basally, with two long and narrow arms nearly evenly separated from base to apices, apices narrowly rounded; ventral lobule shorter and wider than dorsal lobule, acuminate at apex (
<figureCitation box="[1055,1138,1989,2016]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–18" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1224,1249]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,454,1198]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,453,1198]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15–18.Aedeagus of hydrophilids found in the State of Piauí, Brazil. 15, Enochrus (Methydrus) sp.A; 16, Helochares (Sindolus) femoratus (Brullé, 1841); 17–18, Hydrobiomorpha spatula Bachmann, 1988: 17, ventral view; 18, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3762194" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3762194/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="583">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
